\'d8\'a0 Authorizes HPD and HCR to reclassify subsidy payments as capital contributions to registered cooperatives\
\'d8\'a0 Grants tenants full subsidy value accrual rights toward share purchases during the transition period\
\'d8\'a0 Establishes income-restricted resale formulas to preserve affordability\
\'d8 B.2. Amendment to NYS Real Property Law \'a7216 & \'a7220\
\'d8\'a0 Purpose: To allow housing subsidies to satisfy co-op capitalization requirements and to clarify tenant protections under limited-equity conversion.\
\'d8\'a0 Key Additions:\
\'d8\'a0 Language allowing public subsidy disbursements to count as valid consideration in cooperative share agreements\
\'d8\'a0 Protections against equity dilution in the event of subsidy termination\
\'d8\'a0 Eviction moratorium language during co-op conversion if due process procedures are underway\
\'d8 B.3. NYC Ordinance \'97 Creation of \'93Subsidized Limited-Equity Co-op\'94 Status\
\'d8\'a0 Purpose: Establishes a new legal category under NYC Administrative Code for housing units acquired under TCAP.\
\'d8\'a0 Features:\
